  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The risk-benefit of surveillance-protocol biopsy (SPBx) in kidney transplantation remains
      unclear. The study aims to compare outcomes of recipients with SPBx approach to recipients
      with standard approach which allograft biopsy was performed only when indicated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The present randomized-controlled trial in kidney transplant patients aims to compare the
      outcomes and complications between who underwent immunosuppessive drug modification under
      surveillance-protocol biopsy and who underwent immunosuppressive drug modification following
      tough level only.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
